10/12/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Peace Implementation Council's (PIC) steering board hailed the initialling of the Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA) between the EU and BiH at its meeting in Sarajevo on Friday (December 7th). The PIC welcomed the spirit of compromise and unity demonstrated by BiH's political leaders.
Separately, as many as 80% of BiH citizens said they would vote for EU membership if a referendum were held, according to a new poll by the Prism Research agency. The poll, published on Sunday, also found that 70% of the public think BiH lags behind other countries in the region in terms of EU integration. (Nezavisne Novine - 09/12/07; OHR website, Fena, RTRS - 07/12/07)
